genresAdvancedInfo.name: trap boliviano
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Trap Boliviano is a subgenre of trap music that originated in Bolivia. It blends the trap beat with Andean sounds and rhythms, creating a unique and distinct sound. The lyrics often touch on themes of poverty, inequality, and social issues facing the Bolivian youth. Trap Boliviano has gained popularity in recent years and has become an important part of the Bolivian music scene.
